Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored 109 runs in 106 balls.
Aiden Markram made a half-century with 56 runs.
Kagiso Rabada took three wickets for 33 runs.
Marco Jansen took two wickets for 54 runs.
Keshav Maharaj took two wickets for 30 runs.
Marnus Labuschagne was the only top-order batsman for Australia to perform, scoring 46 runs.
Glenn Maxwell took two wickets for 34 runs.
Adam Zampa removed Rassie van der Dussen for 26 runs.
Mitchell Starc took two wickets for 53 runs in the final over.
Post-Match Reflections: Pat Cummins commented on Quinton de Kock's batting and the challenges faced by Australia, noting that their bowlers bowled well but the team was well off the mark.
Cummins mentioned the need to regroup and make amends for the next game.
